President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to designate Eli H. Miller as the Acting United States Director of the Asian Development Bank and the Acting United States Director of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. Miller, who currently serves as Chief of Staff at the Department of the Treasury, will hold these positions until they are filled by appointment or subsequent designation. Prior to his current role, Miller served as the Chief Operating Officer (Finance) for the Donald J. Trump for President Campaign. He holds a Bachelor of Arts from Washington and Jefferson College and a Master in Business Administration from Case Western Reserve University.